author: Eustance Huang
title: Asia Pacific markets set to trade mixed as countries in region continue to battle pandemic
description: Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe declared Tuesday a state of emergency to combat coronavirus infections in major population centers. Singapore also passed a set of laws that bans social gatherings of any size
content:
Stocks in Asia Pacific were set to trade mixed on Wednesday as countries in the region continue to put measures in place to battle the coronavirus pandemic.
